summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Lebanon, particularly 425 (1978), 426 (1978), 1310 (2000), 1337 (2001), and 1365 (2001), 
Welcomes the Secretary-General's report on UNIFIL and endorses his observations and recommendations; 
Extends UNIFIL's mandate for six months, until 31 July 2002; 
Requests the Secretary-General to implement UNIFIL's reconfiguration; 
Supports Lebanon's territorial integrity, sovereignty, and political independence; 
Calls on Lebanon to ensure its effective authority in the south, including deploying armed forces; 
Urges parties to ensure UNIFIL's freedom of movement; 
Encourages a calm environment in the south; 
Reiterates calls on parties to respect the withdrawal line and exercise restraint; 
Condemns violence and breaches of the withdrawal line; 
Supports UNIFIL's efforts to maintain the ceasefire; 
Welcomes demining contributions and encourages further assistance; 
Requests the Secretary-General to consult with Lebanon and concerned parties on resolution implementation; 
Requests a comprehensive report on UNIFIL's activities before the end of the mandate; 
Looks forward to UNIFIL's early fulfilment of its mandate.
Stresses the importance of achieving a comprehensive, just and lasting peace in the Middle East, based on all relevant resolutions, including resolutions 242 (1967) and 338 (1973).
